doc.after: The dollar gross state product for Illinois was estimated to be US$652 billion in 2010.[77] The state's 2010 per capita gross state product was estimated to be US$45,302,[77] the state's per capita personal income was estimated to be US$41,411 in 2009,[78] while the state's taxpayer burden in 2011 was estimated at US$38,500 per taxpayer.[79]
